  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9 and boil a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>cauliflower[s] </strong>into small florets, slice the <strong>stem[s] </strong>and<strong> leaves</strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>cauliflower florets</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook the <strong>florets</strong> for 4-5 min or until tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693916108791-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693916108791-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693916108791-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693916108791-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693916108791-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, drain, the <strong>cauliflower florets</strong>, reserving 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[220ml]</span> <strong>vegetable water </strong>and transfer the <strong>cooked florets</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Reserve the pot</p><p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar flavour block</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>cannellini beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693916112193-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693916112193-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693916112193-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693916112193-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693916112193-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat, once hot add a large knob of <strong>butter alternative</strong></p><p>Once melted, add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk the<strong> reserved vegetable water</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, then add your <strong>creamy single oat </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated cheeze</strong> (save the rest for later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your<strong> cheezy sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1693916117648-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
